		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm thinking about making The Big Switch(TM) to a Mac laptop. The thing is, I haven't had a Mac since the IIGS. (Heh.) Does anyone know if NESASM 3, MagicKit, or other DOS-prompty-looking NESDev things will run on a Mac? Or would it be best to keep my old laptop as a NESDev workstation? I guess I could ask Google, but I'm lazy, and I figure that someone here will know.

		

