<br />I agree; several tools are probably only available as Windows executables, no source code (and not portable even if there were), so running Windows is a good idea. But, you don't have to use it as your main OS, just run it in a virtual machine, almost as another program. <a href="http://www.parallels.com/en/products/desktop/screens&amp;demos/" class="postlink">Parallels</a> is one that integrates Windows programs at the window level.

		

